main event: An unidentified aerial object was observed at Edwards Air Force Base, California on January 23-24, 1968.
interesting points: The object was solid and circular in shape, about the size of a barrack's window.
The object was yellowish in color with fuzzy edges.
The object rose in an upward arc, starting at roof level.
The observation lasted for about 5 minutes.
A control tower operator viewed the object and stated it appeared to be a balloon with a small light attached.
sighted object: A solid, circular object about the size of a barrack's window
witnesses: Airman Kim Degenhardt, Security Police, and a control tower operator
